cells.source: ## Winter Weather Operations Notebook Winter Weather Operations Notebook is a configuration of ArcGIS Notebooks that can be used to automatically start and stop feeds and analytics, reset route status, and truncate previous event's Service Status features from the FieldOperations feature layer when used in conjunction with the Snow Operation Center's Event Manager. When a new event is created, at the next scheduled notebook run-time the script will start all feeds and analytics associated with the Solution before updating the Event "Notebook Status" field to Running. When an active event ends, the script will again update the Event "Notebook Status" field to Stopped once all running feeds and analytics are stopped. This Notebook is meant to be scheduled to run at a regular interval, for example every 15 minutes, by clicking Tasks > Create Task. ### Click Cell > Run All to run this notebook

from arcgis.gis import GIS
import time
gis = GIS("home")
params = {"f": "json"}
velocity_url = None

# Define the item id of the OperationsManagement feature service
operations_management_id = "{{6f072b0ebad74ae9a06ab4569c065956.itemId}}"

# Define the item id of the WinterFieldOperations feature service
field_operations_id = "{{79036430a6274e17ae915d0278b8569c.itemId}}"

# Define the item id of the SnowRoutes feature service
snowroutes_id = "{{f592ca2b671e44be9508162b84ca91c0.itemId}}"

# Define the item id, analytic type and name of the analytics
winter_fleet_tracking = {"id": "{{218436b9a76a46acbe5c0c5752dc18bd.itemId}}", "type": "realtime", "name": "Winter Fleet Tracking"}
snow_route_status = {"id": "{{db4e78dce7ce44398621d131d4977e8f.itemId}}", "type": "bigdata", "name": "Snow Route Status"}


# Number of times to retry starting the analytic
retry = 3

# Get the velocity url from the org
def get_velocity_url():
    subscription_url = "{0}portals/self/subscriptionInfo".format(gis._con.baseurl)
    subscription_info = gis._con.get(subscription_url, params)

    for capability in subscription_info["orgCapabilities"]:
        if capability["id"].lower() == "velocity":
            return capability["velocityUrl"]

# Start a real-time analytic and all associated feeds. Wait on analytic and feeds to successfully start
def start_realtime_analytic(analytic):
    # Get the status of the Analytic
    res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/{2}/status/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"]), params)
    if res["status"].lower() in ["started", "initializing"]:
        print("'{0}' is already running".format(analytic["name"]))
        return None

    # Get all the Feeds used in the Analytic
    feeds = []
    res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/{2}/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"]), params)
    for feed in res["feeds"]:

        #Check if the Feed is already started
        res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/feed/{1}/status/".format(velocity_url, feed["id"]), params)
        if res["status"].lower() in ["started", "initializing"]:
            print("'{0}' is already running".format(feed["label"]))
            continue

        # Start the Feed
        url = "{0}/iot/feed/{1}/start/".format(velocity_url, feed["id"])
        res = gis._con.get(url, params)
        i = 1
        while (res["status"].lower() != "success" and i < retry):
            # Validate and retry if it is not successful
            gis._con.get("{0}/iot/feed/validate/{1}/".format(velocity_url, feed["id"]))
            res = gis._con.get(url, params)
            i += 1

        if res["status"].lower() != "success":
            # If it fails raise an error
            print("{0}' failed to start".format(feed["label"]))
            raise Exception(res)
        feeds.append(feed)

    # Wait on the Feeds to start
    while len(feeds) > 0:
        for feed in [f for f in feeds]:
            res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/feed/{1}/status/".format(velocity_url, feed["id"]), params)
            if "status" not in res or res["status"].lower() == "failed":
                print("'{0}' failed to start".format(feed["label"]))
                raise Exception(res)
            if res["status"].lower() == "started":
                print("'{0}' successfully started".format(feed["label"]))
                feeds.remove(feed)
        time.sleep(2.0)

    # Start the Analytic
    url = "{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/{2}/start/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"])
    res = gis._con.get(url, params)
    i = 1
    while (res["status"].lower() != "success" and i < retry):
        # Validate and retry if it is not successful
        gis._con.get("{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/validate/{2}/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"]))
        res = gis._con.get(url, params)
        i += 1

    if res["status"] != "success":
        # If it fails raise an error
        print("{0}' failed to start".format(analytic["name"]))
        raise Exception(res)

    # Wait on the Analytic to start
    while True:
        res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/{2}/status/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"]), params)
        if "status" not in res or res["status"].lower() == "failed":
            print("'{0}' failed to start".format(analytic["name"]))
            raise Exception(res)
        if res["status"].lower() == "started":
            print("'{0}' successfully started".format(analytic["name"]))
            return
        time.sleep(2.0)

def start_bigdata_analytic(analytic, wait_on_completed=False):
    # Get the status of the Analytic
    res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/{2}/status/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"]), params)
    if res["status"].lower() in ["started", "scheduled", "initializing"]:
        if not wait_on_completed:
            print("'{0}' is already running".format(analytic["name"]))
            return
    else:
        # Start the Analytic
        url = "{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/{2}/start/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"])
        res = gis._con.get(url, params)
        i = 1
        while (res["status"].lower() != "success" and i < retry):
            # Validate and retry if it is not successful
            gis._con.get("{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/validate/{2}/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"]))
            res = gis._con.get(url, params)
            i += 1

        if res["status"] != "success":
            # If it fails raise an error
            print("{0}' failed to start".format(analytic["name"]))
            raise Exception(res)

    # Wait on the Analytic to complete if requested
    while wait_on_completed:
        res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/{2}/status/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"]), params)
        if "status" not in res or res["status"].lower() == "failed":
            print("'{0}' failed to start".format(analytic["name"]))
            raise Exception(res)
        if res["status"].lower() in ["completed", "scheduled"]:
            print("'{0}' successfully ran".format(analytic["name"]))
            return
        time.sleep(2.0)

    print("'{0}' successfully started".format(analytic["name"]))

# Stop an analytic
def stop_analytic(analytic):
    # Check the status of the Analytic
    res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/{2}/status/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"]), params)
    if res["status"].lower() == "stopped":
        print("'{0}' is already stopped".format(analytic["name"]))
    else:
        res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/{2}/stop/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"]), params)
        if "status" not in res or res["status"].lower() != "success":
            raise Exception(res)
        print("'{0}' successfully stopped".format(analytic["name"]))

    # If the Analytic is realtime, stop all the associated feeds
    if analytic["type"] == "realtime":
        res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/analytics/{1}/{2}/".format(velocity_url, analytic["type"], analytic["id"]), params)
        for feed in res["feeds"]:

            #Check if the Feed is already started
            res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/feed/{1}/status/".format(velocity_url, feed["id"]), params)
            if res["status"].lower() == "stopped":
                print("'{0}' is already stopped".format(feed["label"]))
                continue

            # Stop the Feed
            res = gis._con.get("{0}/iot/feed/{1}/stop/".format(velocity_url, feed["id"]), params)
            if res["status"].lower() != "success":
                print("{0}' failed to stop".format(feed["label"]))
                raise Exception(res)
            print("'{0}' successfully stopped".format(feed["label"]))

# Start an event
def start_event():
    # Start the real-time analytics
    for analytic in [winter_fleet_tracking]:
        start_realtime_analytic(analytic)

    # Start the snow route status analytic
    for analytic in [snow_route_status]:
        start_bigdata_analytic(analytic)

# Stop an event
def stop_event():
    # Stop all the analytics
    for analytic in [winter_fleet_tracking, snow_route_status]:
        stop_analytic(analytic)

# Get the Winter Event table and query for the most recent added Winter Event
winter_event_table = gis.content.get(operations_management_id).tables[1]
event = winter_event_table.query(result_record_count=1, return_all_records=False, order_by_fields="created_date DESC")

# Test if there is at least one event in the table
if (len(event.features) > 0):
    # Get the most recent event
    event_record = event.features[0]

    # Get the org's velocity url, only proceed if it is not null
    velocity_url = get_velocity_url()
    if (velocity_url != None):
        # Test if the notebook status is null and the event status is Active, if it is start the event
        if (event_record.attributes["notebookstatus"] == None and event_record.attributes["status"] == "Active"):
            print("Starting Event: {0}".format(event_record.attributes["eventname"]))

            # Truncate the service status feature layer
            service_status_layer = gis.content.get(field_operations_id).layers[0]
            service_status_layer.manager.truncate()

            # Start the analytics and feeds
            start_event()

            # Update the notebook status to Running
            event_record.attributes["notebookstatus"] = "Running"
            winter_event_table.edit_features(updates=[event_record])
            print("Started Event: {0}".format(event_record.attributes["eventname"]))

        # Test if the notebook status is Running and the event status is Past, if it is stop the event
        elif (event_record.attributes["notebookstatus"] == "Running" and event_record.attributes["status"] == "Past"):
            print("Stopping Event: {0}".format(event_record.attributes["eventname"]))

            # Stop the analytics and feeds
            stop_event()

            # Truncate the service status feature layer
            service_status_layer = gis.content.get(field_operations_id).layers[0]
            service_status_layer.manager.truncate()

            # Reset the snow routes feature layer
            snow_routes_layer = gis.content.get(snowroutes_id).layers[0]
            snow_routes_layer.calculate("1=1", [{"field":"lastserviced","sqlExpression":"null"}, {"field":"servicestatus","sqlExpression":"'Not Serviced'"}])

            # Update the notebook status to Stopped
            event_record.attributes["notebookstatus"] = "Stopped"
            winter_event_table.edit_features(updates=[event_record])
            print("Stopped Event: {0}".format(event_record.attributes["eventname"]))

        else:
            print("Event status has not changed")
    else:
        print("Velocity url could not be found for the organization")
else:
    print("No winter events were found")

expressionInfos.expression:
var RoadNm = $feature.roadname
var RoadBw = $feature.roadsbetween
var L = $feature.restrictionslocation
var D = $feature.restrictionsdetails

var roadtxt = iif(isempty(RoadBw)|| RoadBw == " ","For this section of " + RoadNm, RoadNm + ", from " + RoadBw)
var restrictionLocation = iif(isempty(L)|| L == " ",null, " (" + L + ")")
var restrictionDetail = ", " + D + "."

return roadtxt + restrictionLocation + restrictionDetail
